                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14165269" author="hcorg" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 15:34:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached patch. In it only first few digits of generated string are compared. As always: float -&amp;gt; string is a tricky thing...&lt;br/&gt;
I also added (2.5) == &quot;2.5&quot; test which should behave better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165539" author="jensg" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 18:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch. The big question is, however, what is the intention of that test? Is it ok to patch it that way, or should the function being tested be modified? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165576" author="hcorg" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 19:07:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it&apos;s impossible to make toString(floatingPointNo) without precision and expect the get what would human want &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; so this test is really strange&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165614" author="klickverbot" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 19:34:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Konrad: It is quite possible to write a floating point formatting algorithm that doesn&apos;t make those mistakes. However, that was not my intention here, as evidenced by the comment in the code. ctfeToString is only used for the experimental idlgen feature which generates IDL from D types (i.e., the other way round than usual).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Eventually, we will want to ship a CTFE-able floating point formatting routine in the D standard library. I don&apos;t think it is worth the effort to fix this in Thrift before that. Just remove the 3.1415 test, or replace it with a number that works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Interestingly, though, the test definitely passed on x86 and x86_64 half a year ago or so. Apparently, there has been a change to how extra precision is handled in CTFE or something along the lines. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165615" author="jensg" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 19:35:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed Konrad&apos;s patch. At least it solves the actual issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165617" author="klickverbot" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 19:36:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(for anybody interested in how to properly implement this, have a look at Dragon4/Grisu)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165629" author="hudson" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 19:49:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in Thrift #1306 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift/1306/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift/1306/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2775&quot; title=&quot;static assert fails in src/thrift/internal/ctfe.d&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-2775&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-2775&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; static assert fails in src/thrift/internal/ctfe.d (jensg: rev 62d2af7cd3a72ab6f861670503bb16c946d9ca8e)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lib/d/src/thrift/internal/ctfe.d&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14165637" author="hcorg" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 19:58:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, I did know there are algorithms that produce &apos;nicer&apos; output but I didn&apos;t know that Grisu guarantees number1 -&amp;gt; string -&amp;gt; number2 : number1 == number2. Nice. But even it requires expected precision &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;still - for now let&apos;s make test pass, as soon as to!string(double) will work in ctfe whole method and tests could/should be removed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165668" author="hudson" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 20:15:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FAILURE: Integrated in Thrift-Test #50 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift-Test/50/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift-Test/50/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
